headers: Synonymous substitution rate at a site
Non-synonymous substitution rate at a site for the negative/neutral evolution component
Mixture distribution weight allocated to β<sup>-</sup>; loosely -- the proportion of the tree evolving neutrally or under negative selection
Non-synonymous substitution rate at a site for the positive/neutral evolution component
Mixture distribution weight allocated to β<sup>+</sup>; loosely -- the proportion of the tree evolving neutrally or under positive selection
Likelihood ratio test statistic for episodic diversification, i.e., p<sup>+</sup> > 0 <emph>and<emph> β<sup>+</sup> > α
Asymptotic p-value for episodic diversification, i.e., p<sup>+</sup> > 0 <emph>and<emph> β<sup>+</sup> > α
The (very approximate and rough) estimate of how many branches may have been under selection at this site, i.e., had an empirical Bayes factor of 100 or more for the β<sup>+</sup> rate
The total length of branches contributing to inference at this site, and used to scale dN-dS
